Depends: ${misc:Depends}, libgtk-3-0, libblkid1, liblzma5, libsecret-1-0
Recommends: steam
Description: Native GNOME Proton compatibility tool manager
 ProtoGNOME is a native GNOME application for managing Proton
 compatibility tools for Steam on Linux.
 .
 It supports installing and removing GE-Proton, Boxtron, Luxtorpeda,
 SteamTinkerLaunch and other compatibility tools. Unlike ProtonUp-Qt,
 it has no KDE/Qt dependencies and uses Flutter for a native GNOME
 look and feel.
 .
 ProtoGNOME adds the ability to apply a single Proton version to
 ALL games in your Steam library at once.
